r CH2 group) ≠ 1.2 (aldehyde/oxo group). Reparent both terms under GO:0016726 oxidoreductase activity, acting on CH or CH2 groups, NAD or NADP as acceptor (EC:1.17.1.-).\\n\\n- [x] GO:0047111 formate DH (cytochrome) EC:1.17.2.3 — similar wrong-class parent. Re-parent under GO:0016725 oxidoreductase activity, acting on CH or CH2 groups (EC:1.17.-.-) because there is no GO term equivalent to EC:1.17.2.-.\\n\\n- [x] GO:0008839 4-hydroxy-THDP reductase EC:1.17.1.8 i... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n3:   \"comments\": [],\n4:   \"title\": \"Parentage issues within 'oxidoreductase activity' branch\",\n5:   \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31969\"\n6: }\n\n(End of file - total 6 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"body\": \"A Claude review of parentage in the oxidoreductase branch revealed the following issues (I verified them all manually, and made a few more suggestions below - e.g. updated defs to match RHEA):\\n\\n- [x] GO:0102394 '4-hydroxy-L-isoleucine dehydrogenase' EC:1.14.11.45 — the EC is actually L-isoleucine 4-hydroxylase, a 2-OG-dependent dioxygenase. The GO term name is wrong (\\\"dehydrogenase\\\" is a misnomer); consequently it's misparented under GO:0016616 (CH-OH NAD/NADP). Term should be renamed and reparented to GO:0016706.\\n\\n- [x] GO:0050607 'mycothiol-dependent formaldehyde dehydrogenase' EC:1.1.1.306 is under GO:0016620 (EC:1.2.1.-). EC 1.1.1.306 is S-(hydroxymethyl)mycothiol dehydrogenase — it acts on a CH-OH donor, so correct parent is GO:0016616 (EC:1.1.1.-). Also, update name to \\\"S-(hydroxymethyl)mycothiol dehydrogenase activity\\\" to match EC, and update def to \\n\\\"Catalysis of the reaction: S-(hydroxymethyl)mycothiol + NAD+ = S-formylmycothiol + NADH + H+.\\\" using RHEA:28502 as the def xref.\\n\\n- [x] GO:0008762 UDP-N-acetylmuramate dehydrogenase EC:1.3.1.98 is under GO:0016616 (1.1.1.-). Should be under GO:0016628 (CH-CH with NAD/NADP; EC 1.3.1.-). Also update def to \\\"Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-muramate + NADP+ = UDP-N-acetyl-3-O-(1-carboxyvinyl)-alpha-D-glucosamine + NADPH + H+.\\\" and use RHEA:12248 as the def xref.\\n\\n- [x] GO:0008863 formate DH (NAD+) EC:1.17.1.9 and GO:0047899 formate DH (NADP+) EC:1.17.1.10 are under GO:0016620 (EC:1.2.1.-). Formate DH EC class 1.17 (CH or CH2 group) ≠ 1.2 (aldehyde/oxo group). Reparent both terms under GO:0016726 oxidoreductase activity, acting on CH or CH2 groups, NAD or NADP as acceptor (EC:1.17.1.-).\\n\\n- [x] GO:0047111 formate DH (cytochrome) EC:1.17.2.3 — similar wrong-class parent. Re-parent under GO:0016725 oxidoreductase activity, acting on CH or CH2 groups (EC:1.17.-.-) because there is no GO term equivalent to EC:1.17.2.-.\\n\\n- [x] GO:0008839 4-hydroxy-THDP reductase EC:1.17.1.8 i... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n  \"comments\": [],\n  \"title\": \"Parentage issues within 'oxidoreductase activity' branch\",\n  \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31969\"\n}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"__issue_context__.json","time":{"start":1778990705162,"end":1778990705184}},"id":"prt_e341be9e5001ZZiauObi6wq2t6","sessionID":"ses_1cbe431a9ffeF6wJ2aoUeVp53Q","messageID":"msg_e341bcf73001bmr5r969bgpr2i"}}
