{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778990719922,"sessionID":"ses_1cbe431a9ffeF6wJ2aoUeVp53Q","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_WmLf9LKI0AgHUtu0MY8UJTcR","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"jq -r '.body' \"__issue_context__.json\"","timeout":120000,"workdir":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go","description":"Print full issue body"},"output":"A Claude review of parentage in the oxidoreductase branch revealed the following issues (I verified them all manually, and made a few more suggestions below - e.g. updated defs to match RHEA):\n\n- [x] GO:0102394 '4-hydroxy-L-isoleucine dehydrogenase' EC:1.14.11.45 — the EC is actually L-isoleucine 4-hydroxylase, a 2-OG-dependent dioxygenase. The GO term name is wrong (\"dehydrogenase\" is a misnomer); consequently it's misparented under GO:0016616 (CH-OH NAD/NADP). Term should be renamed and reparented to GO:0016706.\n\n- [x] GO:0050607 'mycothiol-dependent formaldehyde dehydrogenase' EC:1.1.1.306 is under GO:0016620 (EC:1.2.1.-). EC 1.1.1.306 is S-(hydroxymethyl)mycothiol dehydrogenase — it acts on a CH-OH donor, so correct parent is GO:0016616 (EC:1.1.1.-). Also, update name to \"S-(hydroxymethyl)mycothiol dehydrogenase activity\" to match EC, and update def to \n\"Catalysis of the reaction: S-(hydroxymethyl)mycothiol + NAD+ = S-formylmycothiol + NADH + H+.\" using RHEA:28502 as the def xref.\n\n- [x] GO:0008762 UDP-N-acetylmuramate dehydrogenase EC:1.3.1.98 is under GO:0016616 (1.1.1.-). Should be under GO:0016628 (CH-CH with NAD/NADP; EC 1.3.1.-). Also update def to \"Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-muramate + NADP+ = UDP-N-acetyl-3-O-(1-carboxyvinyl)-alpha-D-glucosamine + NADPH + H+.\" and use RHEA:12248 as the def xref.\n\n- [x] GO:0008863 formate DH (NAD+) EC:1.17.1.9 and GO:0047899 formate DH (NADP+) EC:1.17.1.10 are under GO:0016620 (EC:1.2.1.-). Formate DH EC class 1.17 (CH or CH2 group) ≠ 1.2 (aldehyde/oxo group). Reparent both terms under GO:0016726 oxidoreductase activity, acting on CH or CH2 groups, NAD or NADP as acceptor (EC:1.17.1.-).\n\n- [x] GO:0047111 formate DH (cytochrome) EC:1.17.2.3 — similar wrong-class parent. Re-parent under GO:0016725 oxidoreductase activity, acting on CH or CH2 groups (EC:1.17.-.-) because there is no GO term equivalent to EC:1.17.2.-.\n\n- [x] GO:0008839 4-hydroxy-THDP reductase EC:1.17.1.8 is under GO:0016628 (EC:1.3.1.-). Class 1.17 ≠ 1.3. Reparent under GO:0016726 oxidoreductase activity, acting on CH or CH2 groups, NAD or NADP as acceptor (EC:1.17.1.-).\n\n- [x] GO:0018525 4-hydroxybenzoyl-CoA reductase EC:1.1.7.1 under GO:0016636 (EC:1.3.7.-). Classes differ. Reparent under GO:0016614 oxidoreductase activity, acting on CH-OH group of donors (EC:1.1.-.-) because there is no GO term equivalent to EC:1.3.7.-. Also, replace defitinon with current RHEA one, \"Catalysis of the reaction: oxidized 2[4Fe-4S]-[ferredoxin] + benzoyl-CoA + H2O = 4-hydroxybenzoyl-CoA + reduced 2[4Fe-4S]-[ferredoxin] + 2 H+.\".\n\n- [x] GO:0044684 dihydromethanopterin reductase EC:1.5.99.15 under GO:0016646 (EC:1.5.1.-). 1.5.99 ≠ 1.5.1. Reparent under GO:0016645 oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-NH group of donors (EC:1.5.-.- ). Also, change def to \"Catalysis of the reaction: 5,6,7,8-tetrahydromethanopterin + acceptor = 7,8-dihydromethanopterin + reduced acceptor.\" to match RHEA:42804, and replace 'GOC:mengo_curators' with RHEA:42804 in def xref (keep the PMID xref).\n\n- [x] GO:0033717 gluconate 2-dehydrogenase (acceptor) EC:1.1.99.3 under GO:0016616 (EC:1.1.1.-). Acceptor-class (.99) ≠ NAD/NADP (.1). Reparent to GO:0016614 oxidoreductase activity, acting on CH-OH group of donors (EC:1.1.-.- ).\n\n- [x] GO:0047081 3-hydroxy-2-methylpyridinecarboxylate dioxygenase [NAD(P)H] activity (EC:1.14.13.242) under GO:0016708 (EC:1.14.12.-). Sub-subclass mismatch. Reparent to GO:0016709 oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen, NAD(P)H as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen (EC:1.14.13.-). Also, rename this term to \"3-hydroxy-2-methylpyridine-5-carboxylate monooxygenase [NAD(P)H] activity\" and change def to \"Catalysis of the reaction: 3-hydroxy-2-methylpyridine-5-carboxylate + NAD(P)H + O2 = 2-(acetamidomethylene)succinate + NAD(P)+.\".\n\n- [x] GO:0106145 scopoletin 8-hydroxylase EC:1.14.11.60 under GO:0016709 (EC:1.14.13.-). Reparent to be under GO:0016706 (EC:1.14.11.-). Also change def to \"Catalysis of the reaction: scopoletin + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 = fraxetin + succinate + CO2.\".\n\n- [x] GO:0016703 (EC:1.13.12.-, internal monooxygenase) is parent of: GO:0010277 chlorophyllide a oxygenase (EC:1.14.13.122), GO:0050588 apo-β-carotenoid dioxygenase (EC:1.13.11.67) — the latter is a dioxygenase under a monooxygenase grouping. Reparent GO:0010277 to GO:0016709 (EC:1.14.13.-) and reparent GO:0050588 to GO:0016702 (EC:1.13.11.-).\n\n- [x] GO:0016706 (EC:1.14.11.-, 2-OG dioxygenase) is parent of: GO:0033759 flavone synthase, GO:0045431 flavonol synthase, GO:0047594 6β-hydroxyhyoscyamine epoxidase, GO:0050589 leucocyanidin oxygenase (all EC:1.14.20.x) — reparent all four under GO:0050498 (EC:1.14.20.-).\n\n- [x] GO:0050498 (EC:1.14.20.-) ironically hosts GO:0102717 DIBOA-glucoside oxygenase EC:1.14.11.59 going the other direction. Reparent to GO:0016706 (EC:1.14.11.-). Also, change def to \"Catalysis of the reaction: DIBOA beta-D-glucoside + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 = TRIBOA beta-D-glucoside + succinate + CO2.\" and use RHEA:32115 as the sole def xef.\n\n- [x] GO:0016709 hosts GO:0050616 secologanin synthase EC:1.14.19.62 - reparent under GO:0016717 (EC:1.14.19.-). Also, change def to \"Catalysis of the reaction: loganin + reduced [NADPH—hemoprotein reductase] + O2 = secologanin + oxidized [NADPH—hemoprotein reductase] + 2 H2O + H+.\" and use RHEA:20585 as the sole def xref.\n\n- [x] GO:0016709 also hosts GO:0102915 piperitol synthase EC:1.14.19.74 — reparent under GO:0016717 (EC:1.14.19.-). Also, change def to \"Catalysis of the reaction: (+)-pinoresinol + reduced [NADPH--hemoprotein reductase] + O2 = (+)-piperitol + oxidized [NADPH--hemoprotein reductase] + 2 H2O + H+. Also catalyzes the synthesis of (+)-sesamin from (+)-piperitol.\"\n\n- [x] GO:0016730 (EC:1.18.-.-, acting on iron-sulfur proteins) hosts GO:0032441 pheophorbide a oxygenase EC:1.14.15.17 — reparent under GO:0016713 (EC:1.14.15.-). Also, change def to \"Catalysis of the reaction: pheophorbide a + 2 reduced [2Fe-2S]-[ferredoxin] + O2 + 2 H(+) = red chlorophyll catabolite + 2 oxidized [2Fe-2S]-[ferredoxin].\" and add RHEA:48140 as a def xref.\n\n- [x] GO:0016709 (EC:1.14.13.-) hosts two EC:1.14.15.x (GO:0004498, GO:0036199) — reparent to GO:0016713 (EC:1.14.15.-).\n\n- [x] GO:0016702 (EC:1.13.11.-) hosts GO:0018570 p-cumate 2,3-dioxygenase EC:1.14.12.25 — wrong EC sub-subclass. Reparent to GO:0016708 (EC:1.14.12.-)\n","metadata":{"output":"A Claude review of parentage in the oxidoreductase branch revealed the following issues (I verified them all manually, and made a few more suggestions below - e.g. updated defs to match RHEA):\n\n- [x] GO:0102394 '4-hydroxy-L-isoleucine dehydrogenase' EC:1.14.11.45 — the EC is actually L-isoleucine 4-hydroxylase, a 2-OG-dependent dioxygenase. The GO term name is wrong (\"dehydrogenase\" is a misnomer); consequently it's misparented under GO:0016616 (CH-OH NAD/NADP). Term should be renamed and reparented to GO:0016706.\n\n- [x] GO:0050607 'mycothiol-dependent formaldehyde dehydrogenase' EC:1.1.1.306 is under GO:0016620 (EC:1.2.1.-). EC 1.1.1.306 is S-(hydroxymethyl)mycothiol dehydrogenase — it acts on a CH-OH donor, so correct parent is GO:0016616 (EC:1.1.1.-). Also, update name to \"S-(hydroxymethyl)mycothiol dehydrogenase activity\" to match EC, and update def to \n\"Catalysis of the reaction: S-(hydroxymethyl)mycothiol + NAD+ = S-formylmycothiol + NADH + H+.\" using RHEA:28502 as the def xref.\n\n- [x] GO:0008762 UDP-N-acetylmuramate dehydrogenase EC:1.3.1.98 is under GO:0016616 (1.1.1.-). Should be under GO:0016628 (CH-CH with NAD/NADP; EC 1.3.1.-). Also update def to \"Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-muramate + NADP+ = UDP-N-acetyl-3-O-(1-carboxyvinyl)-alpha-D-glucosamine + NADPH + H+.\" and use RHEA:12248 as the def xref.\n\n- [x] GO:0008863 formate DH (NAD+) EC:1.17.1.9 and GO:0047899 formate DH (NADP+) EC:1.17.1.10 are under GO:0016620 (EC:1.2.1.-). Formate DH EC class 1.17 (CH or CH2 group) ≠ 1.2 (aldehyde/oxo group). Reparent both terms under GO:0016726 oxidoreductase activity, acting on CH or CH2 groups, NAD or NADP as acceptor (EC:1.17.1.-).\n\n- [x] GO:0047111 formate DH (cytochrome) EC:1.17.2.3 — similar wrong-class parent. Re-parent under GO:0016725 oxidoreductase activity, acting on CH or CH2 groups (EC:1.17.-.-) because there is no GO term equivalent to EC:1.17.2.-.\n\n- [x] GO:0008839 4-hydroxy-THDP reductase EC:1.17.1.8 is under GO:0016628 (EC:1.3.1.-). Class 1.17 ≠ 1.3. Reparent under GO:0016726 oxidoreductase activity, acting on CH or CH2 groups, NAD or NADP as acceptor (EC:1.17.1.-).\n\n- [x] GO:0018525 4-hydroxybenzoyl-CoA reductase EC:1.1.7.1 under GO:0016636 (EC:1.3.7.-). Classes differ. Reparent under GO:0016614 oxidoreductase activity, acting on CH-OH group of donors (EC:1.1.-.-) because there is no GO term equivalent to EC:1.3.7.-. Also, replace defitinon with current RHEA one, \"Catalysis of the reaction: oxidized 2[4Fe-4S]-[ferredoxin] + benzoyl-CoA + H2O = 4-hydroxybenzoyl-CoA + reduced 2[4Fe-4S]-[ferredoxin] + 2 H+.\".\n\n- [x] GO:0044684 dihydromethanopterin reductase EC:1.5.99.15 under GO:0016646 (EC:1.5.1.-). 1.5.99 ≠ 1.5.1. Reparent under GO:0016645 oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-NH group of donors (EC:1.5.-.- ). Also, change def to \"Catalysis of the reaction: 5,6,7,8-tetrahydromethanopterin + acceptor = 7,8-dihydromethanopterin + reduced acceptor.\" to match RHEA:42804, and replace 'GOC:mengo_curators' with RHEA:42804 in def xref (keep the PMID xref).\n\n- [x] GO:0033717 gluconate 2-dehydrogenase (acceptor) EC:1.1.99.3 under GO:0016616 (EC:1.1.1.-). Acceptor-class (.99) ≠ NAD/NADP (.1). Reparent to GO:0016614 oxidoreductase activity, acting on CH-OH group of donors (EC:1.1.-.- ).\n\n- [x] GO:0047081 3-hydroxy-2-methylpyridinecarboxylate dioxygenase [NAD(P)H] activity (EC:1.14.13.242) under GO:0016708 (EC:1.14.12.-). Sub-subclass mismatch. Reparent to GO:0016709 oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen, NAD(P)H as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen (EC:1.14.13.-). Also, rename this term to \"3-hydroxy-2-methylpyridine-5-carboxylate monooxygenase [NAD(P)H] activity\" and change def to \"Catalysis of the reaction: 3-hydroxy-2-methylpyridine-5-carboxylate + NAD(P)H + O2 = 2-(acetamidomethylene)succinate + NAD(P)+.\".\n\n- [x] GO:0106145 scopoletin 8-hydroxylase EC:1.14.11.60 under GO:0016709 (EC:1.14.13.-). Reparent to be under GO:0016706 (EC:1.14.11.-). Also change def to \"Catalysis of the reaction: scopoletin + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 = fraxetin + succinate + CO2.\".\n\n- [x] GO:0016703 (EC:1.13.12.-, internal monooxygenase) is parent of: GO:0010277 chlorophyllide a oxygenase (EC:1.14.13.122), GO:0050588 apo-β-carotenoid dioxygenase (EC:1.13.11.67) — the latter is a dioxygenase under a monooxygenase grouping. Reparent GO:0010277 to GO:0016709 (EC:1.14.13.-) and reparent GO:0050588 to GO:0016702 (EC:1.13.11.-).\n\n- [x] GO:0016706 (EC:1.14.11.-, 2-OG dioxygenase) is parent of: GO:0033759 flavone synthase, GO:0045431 flavonol synthase, GO:0047594 6β-hydroxyhyoscyamine epoxidase, GO:0050589 leucocyanidin oxygenase (all EC:1.14.20.x) — reparent all four under GO:0050498 (EC:1.14.20.-).\n\n- [x] GO:0050498 (EC:1.14.20.-) ironically hosts GO:0102717 DIBOA-glucoside oxygenase EC:1.14.11.59 going the other direction. Reparent to GO:0016706 (EC:1.14.11.-). Also, change def to \"Catalysis of the reaction: DIBOA beta-D-glucoside + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 = TRIBOA beta-D-glucoside + succinate + CO2.\" and use RHEA:32115 as the sole def xef.\n\n- [x] GO:0016709 hosts GO:0050616 secologanin synthase EC:1.14.19.62 - reparent under GO:0016717 (EC:1.14.19.-). Also, change def to \"Catalysis of the reaction: loganin + reduced [NADPH—hemoprotein reductase] + O2 = secologanin + oxidized [NADPH—hemoprotein reductase] + 2 H2O + H+.\" and use RHEA:20585 as the sole def xref.\n\n- [x] GO:0016709 also hosts GO:0102915 piperitol synthase EC:1.14.19.74 — reparent under GO:0016717 (EC:1.14.19.-). Also, change def to \"Catalysis of the reaction: (+)-pinoresinol + reduced [NADPH--hemoprotein reductase] + O2 = (+)-piperitol + oxidized [NADPH--hemoprotein reductase] + 2 H2O + H+. Also catalyzes the synthesis of (+)-sesamin from (+)-piperitol.\"\n\n- [x] GO:0016730 (EC:1.18.-.-, acting on iron-sulfur proteins) hosts GO:0032441 pheophorbide a oxygenase EC:1.14.15.17 — reparent under GO:0016713 (EC:1.14.15.-). Also, change def to \"Catalysis of the reaction: pheophorbide a + 2 reduced [2Fe-2S]-[ferredoxin] + O2 + 2 H(+) = red chlorophyll catabolite + 2 oxidized [2Fe-2S]-[ferredoxin].\" and add RHEA:48140 as a def xref.\n\n- [x] GO:0016709 (EC:1.14.13.-) hosts two EC:1.14.15.x (GO:0004498, GO:0036199) — reparent to GO:0016713 (EC:1.14.15.-).\n\n- [x] GO:0016702 (EC:1.13.11.-) hosts GO:0018570 p-cumate 2,3-dioxygenase EC:1.14.12.25 — wrong EC sub-subclass. Reparent to GO:0016708 (EC:1.14.12.-)\n","exit":0,"description":"Print full issue body","truncated":false},"title":"Print full issue body","time":{"start":1778990719909,"end":1778990719917}},"id":"prt_e341c23180015UpZCVVymIxHJc","sessionID":"ses_1cbe431a9ffeF6wJ2aoUeVp53Q","messageID":"msg_e341c0842001kOnJqF94wTXGe4"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778990719934,"sessionID":"ses_1cbe431a9ffeF6wJ2aoUeVp53Q","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_QphzKGMMw4YhMrk4dxo6ewmw","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/CONTRIBUTING.md","offset":1,"limit":250},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/CONTRIBUTING.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ## Guidelines for creating GitHub tickets with contributions to the ontology:\n2: \n3: 1. **Before you submit a new term request, please check to see if the term already exists:** Before submitting suggestions for new ontology terms, check whether the term already exists, either as a primary term or a synonym. To do this, search the ontology using the [AmiGO](http://amigo.geneontology.org/amigo) browser. If you feel a synonym is missing, or the textual definition of a term needs clarification, please submit a ticket for that. \n4: \n5: 2. **For new term requests:** Please always provide suggestions for a name, definition, position in hierarchy, references (e.g. PMIDs), associated dbxrefs (e.g., GOC:dph, GOC:aruk), and synonyms, if applicable.  The ontology editors can more easily process term requests when all of this information is provided.  For an example, please see the entry for [recycling endosome](http://amigo.geneontology.org/amigo/term/GO:0055037). Provide cross references to external databases such as Rhea, EC, KEGG, MetaCyc and TCBD. \n6: \n7: 3. **For updates to relationships:** Provide details of the current relationships, why you think they are wrong or insufficient, and exactly what should be added or removed.\n8: \n9: 4. **If appropriate, please add a label to your ticket:** The labels menu is to the right of the editing boxes when adding a new issue in github. \n10: \n11: ## Other helpful reminders:\n12: \n13: 1. **Write a detailed request:** Please be specific in your request and include as many details as necessary, providing background information, and if possible, suggesting a solution. GOC editors will be better equipped to address your suggestions if you offer details regarding *'what is wrong'*, *'why'*, and *'how to fix it'*.\n14: \n15: 2. **Provide examples and references:** Please always include references (e.g. PMIDs) for new term requests and, for other term-related requests, include also screenshots, or URLs illustrating the current ontology structure. This will be very helpful to GOC ontology editors, as everyone's settings may be different for their GO browser/editor.\n16: \n17: 3. Tickets with insufficient detail will be marked with a *'More info needed'* label to alert the submitter.\n18: \n19: ### On behalf of the GO editorial team, many thanks!\n20:    \n\n(End of file - total 20 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"## Guidelines for creating GitHub tickets with contributions to the ontology:\n\n1. **Before you submit a new term request, please check to see if the term already exists:** Before submitting suggestions for new ontology terms, check whether the term already exists, either as a primary term or a synonym. To do this, search the ontology using the [AmiGO](http://amigo.geneontology.org/amigo) browser. If you feel a synonym is missing, or the textual definition of a term needs clarification, please submit a ticket for that. \n\n2. **For new term requests:** Please always provide suggestions for a name, definition, position in hierarchy, references (e.g. PMIDs), associated dbxrefs (e.g., GOC:dph, GOC:aruk), and synonyms, if applicable.  The ontology editors can more easily process term requests when all of this information is provided.  For an example, please see the entry for [recycling endosome](http://amigo.geneontology.org/amigo/term/GO:0055037). Provide cross references to external databases such as Rhea, EC, KEGG, MetaCyc and TCBD. \n\n3. **For updates to relationships:** Provide details of the current relationships, why you think they are wrong or insufficient, and exactly what should be added or removed.\n\n4. **If appropriate, please add a label to your ticket:** The labels menu is to the right of the editing boxes when adding a new issue in github. \n\n## Other helpful reminders:\n\n1. **Write a detailed request:** Please be specific in your request and include as many details as necessary, providing background information, and if possible, suggesting a solution. GOC editors will be better equipped to address your suggestions if you offer details regarding *'what is wrong'*, *'why'*, and *'how to fix it'*.\n\n2. **Provide examples and references:** Please always include references (e.g. PMIDs) for new term requests and, for other term-related requests, include also screenshots, or URLs illustrating the current ontology structure. This will be very helpful to GOC ontology editors, as everyone's settings may be different for their GO browser/editor.\n\n3. Tickets with insufficient detail will be marked with a *'More info needed'* label to alert the submitter.\n\n### On behalf of the GO editorial team, many thanks!\n   ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"CONTRIBUTING.md","time":{"start":1778990719813,"end":1778990719933}},"id":"prt_e341c233d0010ZUPv71kiXd77n","sessionID":"ses_1cbe431a9ffeF6wJ2aoUeVp53Q","messageID":"msg_e341c0842001kOnJqF94wTXGe4"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778990719940,"sessionID":"ses_1cbe431a9ffeF6wJ2aoUeVp53Q","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"skill","callID":"call_15LrHw9AQHnI8iSgwSA5G5fw","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"name":"reaction"},"output":"<skill_content name=\"reaction\">\n# Skill: reaction\n\nReaction terms may have mappings that are qualified using skos (using `source` qualifiers), as in the following:\n\n```\n[Term]\nid: GO:0000140\nname: acylglycerone-phosphate reductase (NADP+) activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Catalysis of the reaction: 1-hexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate + NADP+ = 1-hexadecanoylglycerone 3-phosphate + H+ + NADPH.\" [RHEA:17341]\nsynonym: \"1-acyldihydroxyacetone-phosphate reductase activity\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"1-palmitoylglycerol-3-phosphate:NADP+ oxidoreductase activity\" RELATED [EC:1.1.1.101]\nsynonym: \"acyldihydroxyacetone phosphate reductase activity\" RELATED [EC:1.1.1.101]\nsynonym: \"palmitoyl dihydroxyacetone phosphate reductase activity\" RELATED [EC:1.1.1.101]\nsynonym: \"palmitoyl-dihydroxyacetone-phosphate reductase activity\" RELATED [EC:1.1.1.101]\nsynonym: \"palmitoyldihydroxyacetone-phosphate reductase activity\" RELATED [EC:1.1.1.101]\nxref: EC:1.1.1.101 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:ACYLGLYCERONE-PHOSPHATE-REDUCTASE-RXN {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-15046 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: RHEA:17341 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nxref: RHEA:36175 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nis_a: GO:0016616 ! oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-OH group of donors, NAD or NADP as acceptor\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28070\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28526\" xsd:anyURI\n```\n\nIdeally there is a single source of truth for a reaction terms, which should be specified in the def xref\n\nBase directory for this skill: file:///__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/.agents/skills/reaction\nRelative paths in this skill (e.g., scripts/, reference/) are relative to this base directory.\nNote: file list is sampled.\n\n<skill_files>\n\n</skill_files>\n</skill_content>","metadata":{"name":"reaction","dir":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/.agents/skills/reaction","truncated":false},"title":"Loaded skill: reaction","time":{"start":1778990719838,"end":1778990719938}},"id":"prt_e341c2350001FqeZBm6lyBAHiy","sessionID":"ses_1cbe431a9ffeF6wJ2aoUeVp53Q","messageID":"msg_e341c0842001kOnJqF94wTXGe4"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778990719951,"sessionID":"ses_1cbe431a9ffeF6wJ2aoUeVp53Q","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"skill","callID":"call_mfAgPZlUmtwaGyl7qCGmMz9n","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"name":"design-pattern"},"output":"<skill_content name=\"design-pattern\">\n# Skill: design-pattern\n\nDesign Patterns (DPs) are designed to ensure that labels, text definitions (def tags), logical definitions (intersection_of tags) are consistent *within* a term, and *across* terms. i.e. a term \"X development\" uses \"X\" in the label, definition, and logical definition (but prioritizing human readability over robotic conformance); and that \"X development\" terms look similar in form to \"X development\" terms.\n\nDesign patterns are documented here, using the DOSDP system:\n\n`src/patterns/*.yaml`\n\nThis skill should provide documentation in the form of a DESIGN_PATTERNS.md doc (not committed) that document relevant DPs for the task at hand.\n\nDP documentation may be incomplete or out of date, so always check for similar terms / precedent using `obo-grep.pl`.\n\nSide Note: CHEBI has particular rules. Always use the /chemical-entity skill for anything involving chemical entities.\n\n## Example: cell fate commitment\n\nConsider this GO term:\n\n```obo\nid: GO:0001710\nname: mesodermal cell fate commitment\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The cell differentiation process that results in commitment of a cell to become part of the mesoderm.\" [GOC:go_curators, ISBN:0878932437]\nsynonym: \"mesoderm cell fate commitment\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0060795 ! cell fate commitment involved in formation of primary germ layer\nintersection_of: GO:0045165 ! cell fate commitment\nintersection_of: results_in_commitment_to CL:0000222 ! mesodermal cell\nrelationship: part_of GO:0048333 ! mesodermal cell differentiation\n```\n\nThis corresponds to this DP: `src/design_patterns/cell_fate_commitment.yaml`, which defines a variable 'target' that must be a type of cell:\n\n```\nvars:\n  target: \"'cell'\"\nclasses:\n  cell: \"CL:0000000\" # Should ensure plant cells are subclasses\n```\n\nIt also defines lexical patterns:\n\n```\nname:\n  text: \"%s cell fate commitment\"\n```\n\n=> the `name` tag is consistent with this\n\n```\ndef:\n  text: \"The process involved in the commitment of %s cell identity.\"\n```\n\n=> the GO definition varies a little from this but is still essentially consistent\n\nAnd a logical definition pattern:\n\n```\nequivalentTo:\n  text: \"'cell fate commitment' and 'results in commitment of' some %s\"\n  vars:\n    - target\n```\n\nThe OWL expression `equivalentTo G and R some D` maps to\n\n```\nintersection_of: G\nintersection_of: R D\n```\n\n## General guidelines\n\nYou should not add logical definitions unless the term truly corresponds to a DP (or if a user really wants you to). A common anti-pattern is over-specifying logical definition (intersection_of), not realizing these are necessary *and sufficient* conditions. If in doubt, it is better to specify necessary only (is_a and intersection_of).\n\n## Inference of is_a\n\nWhen intersection_of is specified, it's generally not necessary to specify an is_a parent because this can be inferred.\n\nThis can be checked via:\n\n`cd src/ontology && robot reason -i go-edit.obo -o go-edit.entailed.obo` and checking the is_a parent\n\n## Creation of DESIGN_PATTERNS.md doc\n\nThe output of this skill can be a document DESIGN_PATTERNS.md that lists and gives examples from the DP docs and existing ontology precedent, this doc will be used to guide term creation and updates, and to provide justification.\n\nNote this document is temporary, it should not be committed, and do not waste time documenting DPs in *general*, this doc is for specifyng relevant DPs to the *task in hand*\n\nBase directory for this skill: file:///__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/.agents/skills/design-pattern\nRelative paths in this skill (e.g., scripts/, reference/) are relative to this base directory.\nNote: file list is sampled.\n\n<skill_files>\n\n</skill_files>\n</skill_content>","metadata":{"name":"design-pattern","dir":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/.agents/skills/design-pattern","truncated":false},"title":"Loaded skill: design-pattern","time":{"start":1778990719876,"end":1778990719943}},"id":"prt_e341c2368001BXXhQgdkSEXJjJ","sessionID":"ses_1cbe431a9ffeF6wJ2aoUeVp53Q","messageID":"msg_e341c0842001kOnJqF94wTXGe4"}}
